{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypeClassProtocol\/addPrivate(privateSize:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"kind":"symbol","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypeClassProtocol"]]},"metadata":{"role":"symbol","modules":[{"name":"GLibObject"}],"symbolKind":"method","roleHeading":"Instance Method","extendedModule":"GLibObject","title":"addPrivate(privateSize:)","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"addPrivate","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"privateSize"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}],"platforms":[],"externalID":"s:10GLibObject17TypeClassProtocolPAAE10addPrivate11privateSizeySi_tF"},"sections":[],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Registers a private structure for an instantiatable type."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"addPrivate"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"privateSize","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","text":"Int"},{"kind":"text","text":")"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When an object is allocated, the private structures for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the type and all of its parent types are allocated","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"sequentially in the same memory block as the public"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"structures, and are zero-filled."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that the accumulated size of the private structures of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"a type and all its parent types cannot exceed 64 KiB.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This function should be called in the type’s ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"class_init()"},{"text":" function.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The private structure can be retrieved using the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_TYPE_INSTANCE_GET_PRIVATE()"},{"type":"text","text":" macro."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The following example shows attaching a private structure"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"MyObjectPrivate to an object MyObject defined in the standard","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"GObject fashion in the type’s "},{"code":"class_init()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" function.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Note the use of a structure member “priv” to avoid the overhead","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"of repeatedly calling ","type":"text"},{"code":"MY_OBJECT_GET_PRIVATE()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"(C Language Example):"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"C","code":["typedef struct _MyObject        MyObject;","typedef struct _MyObjectPrivate MyObjectPrivate;","","struct _MyObject {"," GObject parent;",""," MyObjectPrivate *priv;","};","","struct _MyObjectPrivate {","  int some_field;","};","","static void","my_object_class_init (MyObjectClass *klass)","{","  g_type_class_add_private (klass, sizeof (MyObjectPrivate));","}","","static void","my_object_init (MyObject *my_object)","{","  my_object->priv = G_TYPE_INSTANCE_GET_PRIVATE (my_object,","                                                 MY_TYPE_OBJECT,","                                                 MyObjectPrivate);","  \/\/ my_object->priv->some_field will be automatically initialised to 0","}","","static int","my_object_get_some_field (MyObject *my_object)","{","  MyObjectPrivate *priv;","","  g_return_val_if_fail (MY_IS_OBJECT (my_object), 0);","","  priv = my_object->priv;","","  return priv->some_field;","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"add_private is deprecated:","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Use the G_ADD_PRIVATE() macro with the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_DEFINE_*"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"family of macros to add instance private data to a type","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glibobject\/typeclassprotocol\/addprivate(privatesize:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"references":{"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/TypeClassProtocol":{"url":"\/documentation\/glibobject\/typeclassprotocol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"TypeClassProtocol"}],"abstract":[{"text":"An opaque structure used as the base of all classes.","type":"text"}],"title":"TypeClassProtocol","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/TypeClassProtocol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"TypeClassProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","type":"topic"},"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject":{"abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject","title":"GLibObject","role":"collection","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glibobject"},"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/TypeClassProtocol/addPrivate(privateSize:)":{"role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","title":"addPrivate(privateSize:)","abstract":[{"text":"Registers a private structure for an instantiatable type.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kin